## Promotion Board

| Nucleus | Recommendation | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Core | HOLD | Strong foundation, but pre-RC and consumer pilot evidence remain gates. |
| Governance | HOLD | High evidence, but governance execution and backend mutation paths remain blocked. |
| Documentation | ADVANCE | Publication authority and versioning consolidation is the selected bounded next cycle; publication remains blocked. |
| Dex | HOLD | Read-only readiness is strong, but functional Dex evolution is paused and execution paths are blocked. |
| Defi | HOLD | Treasury/custody path is critical and not approved for implementation. |
| AxodusAPP | HOLD | Consolidated portfolio intelligence hub; no immediate new cycle selected. |
| Business | HOLD | Already L4 Consolidated; should support the next cycle rather than be reselected. |
| Marketplace | HOLD | Settlement/payment/minting risks require boundary decision first. |
| Academy | HOLD | Rewards/certification/contract boundaries require governance/treasury decision first. |
| Mining | HOLD | Provider/payout/custody boundaries require treasury review first. |
| ACS | HOLD | Execution authority, credentials and runtime autonomy remain critical blockers. |
| Trading | HOLD | Credential vault, exchange execution and withdrawal gates remain critical blockers. |
| BBA-Agency | HOLD | L3 evidence exists; schema and production claim review remain open. |
| Lottery | HOLD | Compliance, randomness, prize and payout gates remain critical blockers. |

## Selected Next Cycle

Selected next cycle: `DOCUMENTATION-EPIC-01 - Publication Authority and Versioning Consolidation`

Meaning:

- consolidate publication ownership, version semantics and approval evidence;
- define source-of-truth precedence, release records and rollback requirements;
- preserve the publication block until separate authority exists.

Non-meaning:

- no publication execution;
- no production backend integration;
- no credentials, signing or mutation;
- no execution authority;
- no production readiness.

