## Nuclei Held And Why

- Core and Governance: foundation/authority tracks; hold for stability and explicit gates.
- Documentation: publication authority and versioning unresolved.
- Dex: read-only readiness complete; functional evolution paused.
- Defi: treasury/custody blockers are critical.
- Marketplace: settlement and payment blockers are critical.
- Academy: reward/certification contract blockers remain.
- Mining: provider/payout/custody blockers remain.
- ACS: execution authority and credential blockers are critical.
- Trading: credential, exchange and withdrawal blockers are critical.
- BBA-Agency: schema/claim review remains open.
- Lottery: compliance/randomness/prize/payout blockers are critical.

## Recommended Sequencing

1. DOCUMENTATION-EPIC-01 publication authority and versioning consolidation.
2. Root global docs versioning/ownership decision.
3. Treasury/Financial Core ownership decision.
4. Governance static read-only transport contract planning.
5. Owner-specific execution boundary reviews only after read-only integration is stable.

## Boundary Statement

This assessment selects a next non-executive planning cycle only. It does not authorize production readiness, implementation, integration execution, governance execution, treasury movement, wallet signing, trading, DEX execution, marketplace settlement, mining payout, lottery payout, ACS provisioning, billing execution, production credentials or on-chain writes.

